      "Filter": {
        "type": "object",
        "desc": "RepositoryFilter is used to filter repositories based on various conditions.\n\n- **Default Behavior**:\n- All fields in a filter are combined with an implicit `And` relationship.\n- For example, if multiple fields like `SourceBranch` and `Status` are provided,\nthe filter will only match repositories that satisfy all specified conditions.\n\n- **Boolean Logic Support**:\n- Use `And`, `Or`, and `Not` fields to construct complex filter logic.\n- Each field accepts one or more nested `RepositoryFilter` objects, allowing for\nrecursive combinations of conditions.\n\n**Examples**:\n1. To filter repositories with `NamespaceName=\"vecode\"` **AND** `ContributorId=\"123\"`, set:\n```json\n{\n\"NamespaceName\": \"vecode\",\n\"ContributorId\": \"123\"\n}\n```\n\n2. To filter repositories with specific properties `department_id=\"123\"` **OR** `byte_tree_node_id=\"456\"`, set:\n```json\n{\n\"Or\": [\n{ \"Property\": { \"Name\": \"department_id\", \"RawValue\": \"123\" } },\n{ \"Property\": { \"Name\": \"byte_tree_node_id\", \"RawValue\": \"456\" } }\n]\n}\n```",
